By Staff
WASHINGTON &mdash; President Trump on Thursday nominated a Philadelphia-based judge, Luis Felipe Restrepo, to a panel that sets federal sentencing guidelines and analyzes trends in federal crimes and punishments.
The Colombia-born Restrepo sits on the Third Circuit Court of Appeals and was originally nominated to the federal bench by former President Barack Obama. He will continue to serve in that position while serving on the U.S. Sentencing Commission, if he is confirmed by the U.S. Senate.
